    "Id": "event_GhostsOfRetribution_Common_TheWeightOfTruth",
    "Name": "The Weight of Truth",
    "Details": "<color=#BFBFBF>It’s been nearly a month since Arelle confirmed it—the Minnesota Tribe is real. Not a ghost story. Not a tech myth. Real, and in motion.\n\nThe Argo’s crew has had time to breathe, plan, resupply. But no one truly relaxed.\n\nNow, a priority hyperpulse message hits the buffer, encrypted in Ghost Bear protocols. It decrypts in seconds—short and sharp.</color>\n\n<color=#DFDFDF>“Return to <i>Melidron</i> at once. Situation has changed. Details can not be shared over hyperpulse.”\n\n—Star Colonel Arelle Jorgensson</color>\n\n<color=#BFBFBF>Sumire lowers the screen, visibly uneasy.</color> “Hell of a tone for a summons.”\n\n<color=#BFBFBF>Darius shifts in his seat, arms crossed.</color> “Could be new intel. Could be a trap. We’ve pissed off a lot of powerful people lately.”\n\n<color=#BFBFBF>Farah just nods grimly.</color> “Something’s about to break loose. I can feel it.”",
    "Icon": "uixTxrSpot_ComputerScreen"
  },
